Seventeen people were injured, on Saturday, when two elephants went on a rampage at a Sri Lankan street pageant. TV footage of the parade shows one of the elephants bolting from a group of people before trampling bystanders as it ran down the road, reports Euronews. Starting from a 600-year-old Buddhist temple, the annual street pageant or Perahera, sees dancers and elaborately decorated elephants parade through the streets of Kotte. READ ALSO:Â Buhari orders evacuation of Nigerians from South Africa According to local media reports, the injured are receiving treatment at the Kalubowila Teaching Hospital, the Colombo General Hospital, and the Sri Jayawardenapura General Hospital. See video: